This challenge is a simple integer overflow. It asks us to “go to the bank” and get the necessary money to “but the flag”. The bank maximum money is 1000 but the flag costs more than this. Note that if the number of money asked is over 1000 we will not be able to get it.
As negative numbers do not trigger the INT_MAX condition, we try to use a -1.
The vulnerability resides on the use of -1 in an unsigned int which will wrap around 4294967295 (assuming unsigned int is 32 bits). Instead when -1 is cast into int, it remains -1.
