The script does the following:
There is a function named transformFlag which :
For each character at position i in the input :

If it’s a lowercase letter it shifts forward by i(mod 26)

res += alphabet[(alphabet_index + i) % 26]

If it’s a digit it shifts it forward by 2*1(mod 10)

res += digits[(digit_index + 2*i) % 10]

If it’s one of these symbols:

S = &quot;!@#$%^&amp;*()_+{}[]|&quot;
It shifts it forward by i*i(mod |S| = 19)
res += S[(S_index + i*i) % len(S)]

If the character doesn’t belong to any set it does nothing

For the inverted flag idvi+1{s6e3{)arg2zv[moqa905+
We just need to use a little python code that reverts this :
def invert_transform(s):
    alpha = &quot;abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz&quot;
    digits = &quot;0123456789&quot;
    sym   = &quot;!@#$%^&amp;*()_+{}[]|&quot;

    out = []
    for i, ch in enumerate(s):
        if ch in alpha:
            out.append(alpha[(alpha.index(ch) - i) % 26])
        elif ch in digits:
            out.append(digits[(digits.index(ch) - 2*i) % 10])
        elif ch in sym:
            out.append(sym[(sym.index(ch) - (i*i)) % len(sym)])
        else:
            # not expected in this challenge
            out.append(ch)
    return &quot;&quot;.join(out)

enc = &quot;idvi+1{s6e3{)arg2zv[moqa905+&quot;
print(invert_transform(enc))

