Now some options to solve the challenge appear, the most interesting is launching the app in an emulator and being able to hook the function with frida in order to intercept the creation of the flag.
For this I will use android-studio emulator for which I will launch a Pixel 4 phone with an Android 11 “R” Version. I install the app and I launch it, only to get this message :

Which means root access will need to be bypassed, here we can see the part on the code that disables the app launch when the device is rooted :
public void onCreate(Bundle bundle) {  
